    "More recent work leverages vision-language pre-trained models such as MDETR (Kamath et al. 2021) and Grounding-DINO (Liu et al.",
    "2024) or multi-task architectures like UniTAB (Yang et al. 2022) and OFA (Wang et al.",
    "2022) to boost open-set grounding, at the expense of greater data and compute requirements.Multimodal Large Language Model.",
    "Multimodal large language models (MLLMs) unify vision and language for a range of tasks.",
    "Flamingo (Team 2022) and BLIP-2 (Li et al. 2023) align visual and textual representations via crossattention or Q-Former modules."
